Create the Customer Insights App

You create an app from the Customer Insights template. Schedule the app's data sync and recipes.

Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition. Requires a CRM Analytics Growth or CRM Analytics Plus license.

To create and manage the app: Manage CRM Analytics Templated Apps
To use CRM Analytics templated apps: Use CRM Analytics Templated Apps

The Customer Insights app is created by default when you enabled CRM Analytics. If the app is missing, install it using these instructions or enable auto-installation of apps in Setup.

Before creating an app, ensure that:

Your org has at least one record of each of these objects: User, Account, and Opportunity.
The Analytics Integration User has the appropriate Salesforce field-level security to view the fields you want to analyze.

Create the App

In the Analytics tab or Analytics Studio, click Create and select App. Choose whether to create an app or use settings from an existing app, and click Continue.

If your org meets the minimum requirements, click Looks good, next. Give your app a name, and click Create.

CRM Analytics takes a few minutes to create your app. You can track its progress on the page that displays. When you see the Application Complete! message, refresh the page.

Schedule the Data Sync

In Analytics Studio, click the gear icon in the upper right and select Data Manager. Set a time to run the data sync, outside normal working hours if desired. Save your changes.

Schedule When to Run the Recipes

The app creates several recipes that you must schedule. Make sure that the data is synced before running the recipes.
title: Guided Setup: Creating the Customer Insights App
